Pre-Game Insights: Namibia aim to continue their undefeated start to World Cup qualifying when they host Tunisia.
Namibia could leapfrog Tunisia if they secure maximum points.
Namibia's last win over Tunisia was in January, and they have not scored in their last five matches.
Tunisia could create separation from Namibia with a win, having not conceded in World Cup qualifying so far.
Tunisia's goal-scoring threat has been limited, with Mohamed Ali Ben Romdhane's goal coming from the penalty spot.
